-- Akzo, Edison, Legrand, Pernod, STMicroelectronics: Europe Equity Preview
-- Stephanie Borise
-- 2010-07-23T04:00:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/akzo-edison-legrand-pernod-stmicroelectronics-europe-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the last close.  
 The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  rose 2.1 percent to 254.37. The
 Stoxx 50 Index  gained 2.1 percent to 2,463.26. The  Euro Stoxx 50
Index , a benchmark for nations using the euro, climbed 2.8
percent to 2,714.21.  
 Akzo Nobel NV  (AKZA NA): The world’s biggest paint maker
may report second-quarter net income rose to 192.3 million
euros, the average of nine analyst  estimates  compiled by
Bloomberg, from 155 million euros a year earlier. Akzo Nobel
increased 1.8 percent to 44.29 euros.  
 Alstom SA  (ALO FP): The world’s third-largest power-
equipment maker won two contracts worth 450 million euros ($580
million) to design, build and maintain two combined cycle gas
units for GVK Industries in India. The French company’s shares
added 2.8 percent to 37.17 euros.  
 Edison SpA (EDN IM): Italy’s second-largest power generator
plans to report first-half results. The stock increased 0.7
percent to 92.1 cents.  
 Legrand SA  (LR FP): The French maker of electrical switches
and plugs made an offer to buy Indo Asian Fusegear Ltd.’s
switchgear division. The companies didn’t disclose financial
terms. The shares rose 4.8 percent to 25.22 euros.  
 Pernod Ricard SA  (RI FP): The maker of Absolut vodka and
Chivas Regal whiskey raised its full-year profit forecast for
the second time. Profit from recurring operations will rise 3
percent to 4 percent this year, up from a previous estimate of
growth of about 3 percent. Sales excluding revenue from
acquisitions advanced “close to 3 percent” in the fiscal
fourth quarter. The shares added 2 percent to 64.11 euros.  
 STMicroelectronics NV  (STM IM): Europe’s largest chipmaker
plans to hold a conference call on second-quarter results. The
stock advanced 2.3 percent to 6.75 euros.  
